Peraeopods 3 to 7 simple; merus, carpus and propodus posterior margins with clusters of 2–3 cuspidate setae with accessory setae, cluster of simple setae on anterior and posterior borders; peraeopods 3 to 7 dactylus less than half-length of propodus; peraeopods 3 to 6 with similar size and peraeopod 7 slightly longer; coxal plates of peraeopod 3, 5, 6 and 7 wider than longer, with small simple setae on margin; peraeopod 4 coxal plate excavated posteriorly and slightly wider than longer (
