The main environmental impacts that can interfere with the local biodiversity of the Cachoeira Grande watershed are related to the urban occupation around the MNLP. On the other hand, around the main rivers and streams of the Ribeirão Grande watershed, there is a development of subsistence agriculture by traditional families (that already occupied the area before the implementation of the UC) with small plantations of banana, beans, cassava, corn, and others, plus small livestock (
Schmitt et al . 2019
). However, it is noteworthy that the streams sampled have riparian vegetation along its entire extension.
